      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Substantive due process is a crucial legal doctrine that protects fundamental individual liberties from government overreach, ensuring that the government cannot infringe upon basic rights even if it follows proper procedures. This concept has been instrumental in expanding rights by striking down laws that infringe on personal autonomy, such as those related to privacy and marriage equality. It serves as a vital check on government power, safeguarding the core freedoms that define a free society.",
      "source": "target",
